cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper presents a deep learning-based approach for left ventricle segmentation in cardiac MRI images. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a novel dynamic-based labeling scheme and uses a policy model to guide an agent, which involves reinforcement learning techniques, indicating that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on two datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses the magnitude difference of the Poincaré map as a stopping criterion, which indicates that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
